# Keep the Docker build context small and avoid leaking host artefacts
# or secrets into the image. The builder stage only needs the workspace
# Cargo manifests, lockfile, source tree under `crates/`, and `deny.toml`.

# --- Build artefacts ---------------------------------------------------------
# `target/` on the host can be many GiB; never ship it to the daemon.
target/
**/target/

# --- VCS / CI metadata ------------------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.github
.gitattributes

# --- Editor / IDE state -----------------------------------------------------
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store

# --- Docs / non-source ------------------------------------------------------
# These don't influence the binary; excluding them shrinks the context
# and avoids cache-busting on doc-only edits.
README.md
CHANGELOG.md
SECURITY.md
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md
LICENSE-MIT
LICENSE-APACHE
docs/
install/
scripts/

# --- Local config / secrets -------------------------------------------------
# rustydns.toml is mounted at runtime under /etc/rustydns/rustydns.toml.
# Never bake an operator's config (which may contain DoH tokens) into the
# image.
rustydns.toml
rustydns.example.toml
*.pem
*.key
*.crt

# --- Container infra itself -------------------------------------------------
# The Dockerfile is read by the daemon (`docker build`), not by the build
# context tar.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
